  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 12.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Sanctify yourselves, both ye and your brethren",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Nothing of the appointed observances of the Law are to be omitted this time, as in the haste and want of premeditation of the former occasion (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 19:22",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 28:41",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 40:13",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Leviticus 8:12",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Leviticus 20:7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Leviticus 21:8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 5:11",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 29:15",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). These \"sanctifyings\" consisted of different observances, according to the person and the occasion, but largely of ablutions of the body, washing of the clothes, and keeping separate from all natural and ceremonial causes of uncleanness in ordinary cases of Levitical service. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "That ye may bring up the ark",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The word here employed for \"bring\" is not the same with the \"carry\" of vers 1 and 2. But the following verses (13-15) seem to intimate that, whatever the exact reason for which Uzzah had been peremptorily cut off, the Levites had also been to blame in not sanctifying themselves to ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "carry",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " the ark by its staves in the way originally appointed. 1 Chronicles 15:12",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Keil and Delitzsch Biblical Commentary on the Old Testament",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Zadok of the line of Eleazar (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 6:1-15",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), and Abiathar of the line of Ithamar, were the heads of the two priestly lines, and at that time both held the office of high priest (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 24:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Samuel 15:24",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "., ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Samuel 20:25",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). These priests and the six princes of the Levites just enumerated were charged by David to consecrate themselves with their brethren, and to bring up the ark of God to the place prepared for it. התקדּשׁ, to consecrate oneself by removal of all that is unclean, washing of the body and of the clothes (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Genesis 35:2",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), and careful keeping aloof from every defilement, avoiding coition and the touching of unclean things; cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 19:10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 19:15",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". לו אל־כינותי, to (the place) which I have prepared for it. לו הכינותי is a relative clause with אשׁר, construed with a preposition as though it were a substantive: cf. similar constructions, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 29:3",
